<list list-type="bullet"><list-item><p>“Figure 1. Generalized workflow from incidence object construction to modeling and visualization.” - The first example in the paper is using a line-list format as data inputs but showed a stratified graphic. To be consistent and easier to follow for the reader, this figure illustrates the flow of such of data type, knowing that line-list is the primary source of epidemiological surveillance. A solution present in the figure is the two types of data inputs (non-aggregated/aggregated count). It would be easier, from a reader point of view, to capture the data flow from the line-lit to the final products proposed by this package.</p></list-item></list> Comment 20:
